abstract: Lawyers for the Food and Drug Administration backed an industry effort to block New York City’s calorie labeling law in restaurants and food stores.
snippet: Lawyers for the Food and Drug Administration backed an industry effort to block New York City’s calorie labeling law in restaurants and food stores.
lead_paragraph: The Food and Drug Administration has filed court papers in support of an effort to overturn a New York City law requiring calorie counts to be posted by certain establishments — at least the second time the Trump administration has inserted itself into a local case.

abstract: Three corporate chiefs have stepped down from an advisory council to the president. The question is, will more follow?
snippet: Three corporate chiefs have stepped down from an advisory council to the president. The question is, will more follow?
lead_paragraph: By late Monday, in the immediate aftermath of the violence in Charlottesville, Va., the number of corporate chiefs serving as advisers to President Trump had shrunk by three. The question is, will more follow?

abstract: After a legal fight with the original builder, the developers of the New York Wheel hope to get back on track with a new construction team.
snippet: After a legal fight with the original builder, the developers of the New York Wheel hope to get back on track with a new construction team.
lead_paragraph: New York City may still get its giant Ferris wheel, but it is unclear when it might start spinning.

lead_paragraph: KAUAI, Hawaii — If Pierre Omidyar gets his way, 699 dairy cows will soon enjoy a glorious view of the Pacific Ocean, framed by a pristine beach.

abstract: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo is advocating new tolls on some of the city’s busiest areas, a plan that could generate millions of dollars for repairing the subway.
snippet: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo is advocating new tolls on some of the city’s busiest areas, a plan that could generate millions of dollars for repairing the subway.
lead_paragraph: A decade ago, Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York offered a plan to ease traffic in Manhattan and raise hundreds of millions of dollars to improve the city’s aging infrastructure. Drivers would be charged $8 to enter the most congested parts of Manhattan during peak commuting hours.

abstract: Associates of Xiao Jianhua, who disappeared from Hong Kong’s Four Seasons Hotel in January, helped Dalian Wanda with a share sale and privatization.
snippet: Associates of Xiao Jianhua, who disappeared from Hong Kong’s Four Seasons Hotel in January, helped Dalian Wanda with a share sale and privatization.
lead_paragraph: Dalian Wanda, the Chinese conglomerate that owns the AMC movie theater chain and nurtures Hollywood ambitions, has sometimes turned to the secretive business network of a politically connected Chinese billionaire in times of need.

abstract: The plan, which is meant to revive what was once the core of corporate activity in the city, is likely to make the area more densely packed while yielding upgrades to subway stations and public spaces.
snippet: The plan, which is meant to revive what was once the core of corporate activity in the city, is likely to make the area more densely packed while yielding upgrades to subway stations and public spaces.
lead_paragraph: The City Council on Wednesday unanimously approved a rezoning for a section of Midtown Manhattan that is likely to make the area even more densely packed with high-rise office buildings but that promises to yield improvements to subway stations and public spaces.
